, \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"inspiration\", \"from\": 958, \"to\": 969}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 975, \"to\": 990}, {\"ngram\": \"his nearly four-hour production\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1025}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1037, \"to\": 1042}, {\"ngram\": \"rain\", \"from\": 1057, \"to\": 1061}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The scene, intended to promote tolerance of different sexual and gender identities, also featured French actor Philippe Katerine who appeared almost naked and painted blue as Dionysus, the Greek god of wine and pleasure.\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1306, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9784857155019074, \"rank\": 0.021828931967477323, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1197, \"end\": 1214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philippe Katerine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\"}, {\"begin\": 1261, \"end\": 1269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.687088969618008e-19, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 1275, \"end\": 1280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.6079468441862366, \"rank\": 0.6376717287612226, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/res