at affirms our Republican values of liberty, equality and fraternity,\\\" he added.\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1657, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1592, \"end\": 1602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Spanish_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9256223905024473, \"rank\": 0.0803504438205858, \"text\": \"Republican\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Spanish_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Spanish_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a ceremony\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1508}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1527}, {\"ngram\": \"a ceremony\", \"from\": 1564, \"to\": 1574}, {\"ngram\": \"liberty\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1620}, {\"ngram\": \"equality\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1630}, {\"ngram\": \"fraternity\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1645}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In one of the other striking moments of the ceremony, a woman holding a bloodied severed head and intended to be executed French queen Marie-Antoinette appeared in a window of the Conciergerie, a building where she was imprisoned after the 1789 French Revolution.\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1922, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1781, \"end\": 1787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9784857155019074, \"rank\": 0.021828931967477323, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1794, \"end\": 1810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.594210195171564e-44, \"text\": \"Marie-Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}, {\"begin\": 1839, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4928559987731061e-36, \